# Insurance Claims Processing - Dependencies
# For Microsoft Foundry Agents Workshop
#
# =============================================================================
# SOURCE OF TRUTH for dependencies. Regenerate the lock with:
#   pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt
# Workshop attendees install the *locked* file: pip install -r requirements.txt
#
# DRIFT RULE — keep these in sync to avoid hosted-vs-notebook conflicts:
#   The hosted agents (hosted-agents/*/requirements.txt) MUST use the SAME
#   agent-framework[foundry] and agent-framework-foundry-hosting versions as
#   pinned below. The Agent Framework family is pre-release and breaks often,
#   so it is pinned with == (not >=). After bumping it here, update both
#   hosted-agents/benefits-*/requirements.txt to match, then redeploy.
#   Hosted runtime must be Python 3.14 (3.13 fails the hyperlight wheel).
# =============================================================================

